<title>SPAIN: Spain's CNMV continues Endesa probe.</title>
<headline>Spain's CNMV continues Endesa probe.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-06-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spain's Stock Market Commission CNMV is continuing its investigation into the use of privileged information by individuals in a case tied to utility Endesa's purchase of two regional utilities last year.</p>
<p>The investigation centres on 66.8 percent state-owned Endesa's controversial purchase late last year of regional utilities Sevillana de Electricidad and Fuerzas Electricas de Catalunya.</p>
<p>In the case, the CNMV has already fined leading Spanish utility Endesa 300 million pesetas and second-largest bank Banco Bilbao Vizcaya 85 million pesetas in the same case for improper use of information.</p>
<p>&quot;After a detailed investigation...the inspectors have identified a number of cases in which there is the suspicions that information could have been used inappropriately,&quot; CNMV chairman Juan Fernandez-Armesto said on Monday.</p>
<p>--Madrid Newsroom +34 1 585 2167</p>
